article.headline: Lafayette 78, Lehigh 60
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Bilal Abdullah had 18 points and 13 rebounds to lead Lafayette to a 78-60 win over Lehigh on Saturday. Matt Betley and Andrew Brown added 13 points apiece for Lafayette (15-12, 6-6 Patriot League). Bryan White had 18 points in the loss for Lehigh (12-14, 5-7). Lehigh led by as many as eight in the first half, but the Leopards charged ahead on a 25-7 run and went into the break with a 33-23 lead. Lafayette turned it into a blowout by shooting 61 percent in the second half. The Mountain Hawks at one point went more than 10 minutes without scoring and shot 36 percent for the game. Marquis Hall and Rob Keefer each added nine points for Lehigh.
